[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API","text":"This page renders the function docstrings for the public API.\n\nFor mathematical definitions and worked usage examples, see Math and Usage.","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Core-Evaluation","page":"API","text":"","title":"Core Evaluation"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Analysis-and-Diagnostics","page":"API","text":"","title":"Analysis and Diagnostics"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Jacobians","page":"API","text":"","title":"Jacobians"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Root-Finding","page":"API","text":"","title":"Root Finding"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.smn","page":"API","text":"Compute angular spheroidal wave functions and derivatives with respect to eta.\n\nUse this for batched angular evaluations for real or complex c.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.smn"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.rmn","page":"API","text":"Compute radial spheroidal wave functions and derivatives with respect to x.\n\nSupports radial kinds 1-4 and returns complex-valued outputs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.rmn"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.eigenvalue","page":"API","text":"Compute the spheroidal separation constant lambda_mn(c).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.eigenvalue"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.accuracy","page":"API","text":"Return backend-estimated decimal-digit accuracy for angular or radial evaluations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.accuracy"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.radial_wronskian","page":"API","text":"Compute the radial Wronskian diagnostic from kind-1 and kind-2 radial solutions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.radial_wronskian"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jacobian_eigen","page":"API","text":"Estimate numerical Jacobian of eigenvalue with respect to c.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jacobian_eigen"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jacobian_smn","page":"API","text":"Estimate numerical Jacobian of smn outputs with respect to c.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jacobian_smn"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jacobian_rmn","page":"API","text":"Estimate numerical Jacobian of rmn outputs with respect to c.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jacobian_rmn"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.find_c_for_eigenvalue","page":"API","text":"Solve eigenvalue(m, n, c) = lambda_target for real c using a bracketed hybrid solver.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.find_c_for_eigenvalue"},{"category":"section","location":"backend-overrides/#Backend-Overrides","page":"Backend Overrides","text":"This page describes how backend library paths are selected and how users can override them.","title":"Backend Overrides"},{"category":"section","location":"backend-overrides/#Resolution-Order","page":"Backend Overrides","text":"At module initialization, backend libraries are resolved in this order:\n\nPackage artifacts from Artifacts.toml (default user path)\nEnvironment variables\nLocal generated config file deps/library_config.jl (developer fallback)\n\nAt runtime, explicit API calls always take precedence over automatic initialization:\n\nset_backend_library!(\"/path/to/lib\"; precision=:double)\nset_backend_library!(\"/path/to/lib\"; precision=:quad)","title":"Resolution Order"},{"category":"section","location":"backend-overrides/#Environment-Variables","page":"Backend Overrides","text":"Set one or both variables before starting Julia:\n\nSPHEROIDALWAVEFUNCTIONS_LIBRARY_R8 for double precision backend\nSPHEROIDALWAVEFUNCTIONS_LIBRARY_R16 for quad precision backend\n\nWindows PowerShell example:\n\n$env:SPHEROIDALWAVEFUNCTIONS_LIBRARY_R8 = \"C:\\path\\to\\spheroidal_batch_r8.dll\"\n$env:SPHEROIDALWAVEFUNCTIONS_LIBRARY_R16 = \"C:\\path\\to\\spheroidal_batch_r16.dll\"\njulia\n\nLinux/macOS shell example:\n\nexport SPHEROIDALWAVEFUNCTIONS_LIBRARY_R8=\"/path/to/libspheroidal_batch_r8.so\"\nexport SPHEROIDALWAVEFUNCTIONS_LIBRARY_R16=\"/path/to/libspheroidal_batch_r16.so\"\njulia","title":"Environment Variables"},{"category":"section","location":"backend-overrides/#Programmatic-Override","page":"Backend Overrides","text":"Use explicit runtime configuration when paths are known inside application code:\n\nusing SpheroidalWaveFunctions\n\nset_backend_library!(\"/path/to/libspheroidal_batch_r8.so\"; precision=:double)\nset_backend_library!(\"/path/to/libspheroidal_batch_r16.so\"; precision=:quad)","title":"Programmatic Override"},{"category":"section","location":"backend-overrides/#Inspect-Active-Paths","page":"Backend Overrides","text":"backend_library(precision=:double)\nbackend_library(precision=:quad)","title":"Inspect Active Paths"},{"category":"section","location":"backend-overrides/#Notes","page":"Backend Overrides","text":"Artifact entries must be populated for true out-of-box backend loading on fresh systems.\nIf artifacts are missing for a platform, package import attempts a one-time local build automatically.\ndeps/library_config.jl is generated locally by build tooling and is intentionally gitignored.\nIf a configured path does not exist, it is ignored and a warning is emitted.\nIf no backend is configured for a requested precision, calls fail with a clear error message.","title":"Notes"},{"category":"section","location":"#SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jl","page":"Home","text":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jl provides fast Julia bindings to native Fortran kernels for spheroidal wave computations.","title":"SpheroidalWaveFunctions.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Public-API","page":"Home","text":"smn\nrmn\neigenvalue\naccuracy\nradial_wronskian\njacobian_eigen\njacobian_smn\njacobian_rmn\nfind_c_for_eigenvalue","title":"Public API"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"using SpheroidalWaveFunctions\n\neta = [-0.5, 0.0, 0.5]\nx = [1.1, 1.2]\n\ns = smn(0, 2, 20.0, eta; spheroid=:prolate, precision=:double)\nr = rmn(0, 1, 20.0, x; spheroid=:prolate, precision=:double, kind=1)\n\nlambda = eigenvalue(0, 2, 20.0; spheroid=:prolate, precision=:double)\nacc = accuracy(0, 2, 20.0, eta; target=:angular)\nW = radial_wronskian(0, 1, 20.0, x; spheroid=:prolate, precision=:double)\n\nj_lambda = jacobian_eigen(0, 1, 20.0; with_metadata=true)\nroot = find_c_for_eigenvalue(0, 1, lambda; bracket=(1.0, 40.0))\n\nSee the API page for signatures and docstrings, and Math and Usage for equations and conventions.","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Mathematical-Basis-and-Usage","page":"Math and Usage","text":"This page summarizes the mathematical model and practical usage for all public operations.","title":"Mathematical Basis and Usage"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Shared-Separation-Structure","page":"Math and Usage","text":"Angular and radial spheroidal equations share the separation constant lambda_mn(c).\n\nm: order with m >= 0\nn: degree with n >= m\nc: size parameter (real or complex)","title":"Shared Separation Structure"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Angular-Function-smn","page":"Math and Usage","text":"smn computes the angular spheroidal function and its derivative in eta.\n\nfracddetaleft(1-eta^2)fracdS_mndetaright\n+left(lambda_mn(c)-c^2(1-eta^2)-fracm^21-eta^2right)S_mn=0","title":"Angular Function smn"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Radial-Function-rmn","page":"Math and Usage","text":"rmn computes radial spheroidal functions and derivatives in x for selected kind.\n\nfracddxleft(x^2-1)fracdR_mndxright\n+left(lambda_mn(c)-c^2x^2-fracm^2x^2-1right)R_mn=0","title":"Radial Function rmn"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Wronskian-Diagnostic-radial_wronskian","page":"Math and Usage","text":"The radial diagnostic uses:\n\nmathscrW(x)=R_1(x)R_2(x)-R_1(x)R_2(x)\n\nIn a stable regime, the Wronskian should be approximately constant versus x.","title":"Wronskian Diagnostic radial_wronskian"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Eigenvalue-eigenvalue","page":"Math and Usage","text":"Returns lambda_mn(c) used in both separated equations.\n\nAt spherical limit:\n\nlambda_mn(0)=n(n+1)","title":"Eigenvalue eigenvalue"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Accuracy-accuracy","page":"Math and Usage","text":"Returns per-point backend-estimated decimal digits.\n\ntarget=:angular\ntarget=:radial\n\nUse these values as solver-quality indicators for downstream acceptance criteria.","title":"Accuracy accuracy"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Jacobians","page":"Math and Usage","text":"The Jacobians are numerical derivatives with respect to c.\n\njacobian_eigen\njacobian_smn\njacobian_rmn\n\nFor real c, centered difference uses:\n\nf(c)approxfracf(c+h)-f(c-h)2h\n\nFor complex c = a + ib, partials are computed separately with respect to a and b.","title":"Jacobians"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Reliability-Metadata","page":"Math and Usage","text":"With with_metadata=true, Jacobian APIs return derivative quality fields:\n\nstep_used\nrelative_change_when_halving_step\nfinite_flag\nconditioning_flag\nsuggested_action\n\nThese fields support robust root-finding and inverse workflows.","title":"Reliability Metadata"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Root-Finding","page":"Math and Usage","text":"find_c_for_eigenvalue solves the scalar inverse problem:\n\nlambda_mn(c) - lambda_texttarget = 0\n\nusing a bracketed hybrid method with bisection fallback and optional Jacobian acceleration.\n\nExample:\n\nlambda_target = eigenvalue(0, 1, 30.0; spheroid=:prolate, precision=:double)\nroot = find_c_for_eigenvalue(0, 1, lambda_target;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t bracket=(10.0, 50.0),\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t spheroid=:prolate,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t precision=:double)","title":"Root Finding"},{"category":"section","location":"math-and-usage/#Full-Reference","page":"Math and Usage","text":"For the complete long-form theory-and-usage narrative, see docs/mathematical-basis-and-usage.md in the repository.","title":"Full Reference"}]
